commit.message: Fix links to repository in README.rst

Conversion changes

- Run black, isort
- Stricter flake8 with fixes
- Add pre-commit hooks
- Change repository details
- Update copyright dates
Added tag macholib-1.13 for changeset b5ca8a524620

Add two new load commands introduced in macOS 10.15

Fixes #31
Add python 3.8 and 3.9 to test matrix
Fix #27: Missing describe method for build_version_command

This adds a crude hack to deal with dylibs/extensions found in Python binary wheels

Those wheels are relocatable using @loader_path paths in binaries and
commonly have load commands with too little space for the regular
rewrite process.

This is intended to be a quick hack until macholib gets proper support
for @loader_path.
Some updates on support for new load commands
Updates to pass tests on macOS 10.14
Do not use standard section for metadata
